        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 5:15PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Smith, or 15 miles east of Gardnerville, moving
north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Como, Artesia Lake, Mount Siegel, and Smith Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
